  "text": "## Certificate Validation in Envoy TLS v1.31.2\n\nThis audit identifies four key C++ source files in the Envoy proxy (envoyproxy/envoy v1.31.2) that handle TLS certificate validation logic:\n\n### Key Files Identified:\n\n1. **source/extensions/transport_sockets/tls/cert_validator/spiffe/spiffe_validator.cc**\n   - Contains SPIFFE-specific certificate validation implementation\n   - Uses `X509_verify_cert()` at line 177 in method `verifyCertChainUsingTrustBundleStore()`\n   - Implements `addClientValidationContext()` at line 108 for client certificate setup using `SSL_CTX_set_client_CA_list()`\n   - Implements `initializeSslContexts()` at line 145 returning verification mode flags\n   - Validates both server certificates (through peer certificate chains) and supports client certificate validation\n\n2. **source/common/tls/utility.cc**\n   - Utility functions for certificate verification\n   - Contains `getX509VerificationErrorInfo()` at line 457 which uses `X509_verify_cert_error_string()` at line 462\n   - Provides error reporting and certificate information extraction utilities used throughout validation pipeline\n\n3. **source/common/tls/context_impl.cc**\n   - Core SSL/TLS context implementation\n   - Uses `SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify()` at line 181 to configure custom certificate verification callback\n   - Implements `customVerifyCallback()` at line 474 as the custom verification callback\n   - Implements `customVerifyCertChain()` at line 512 for asynchronous certificate validation\n   - Uses `SSL_CTX_get_verify_mode()` at line 683 to check verification mode\n   - Delegates actual verification to cert_validator_ instance\n   - Handles both incoming (client) and outgoing (server) certificate verification through the verification callback mechanism\n\n4. **source/common/tls/cert_validator/default_validator.cc**\n   - Default certificate validator implementation\n   - Uses `SSL_CTX_set_verify()` at line 528 in `addClientValidationContext()` with `SSL_VERIFY_PEER | SSL_VERIFY_FAIL_IF_NO_PEER_CERT` flags for client certificate validation\n   - Uses `X509_verify_cert()` at line 315 in `doVerifyCertChain()` for server certificate chain verification against trust store\n   - Implements `initializeSslContexts()` at line 56 to set up verification modes based on configuration\n   - Implements `addClientValidationContext()` at line 481 to configure client certificate validation including trust CA setup and verification depth\n   - Implements `doVerifyCertChain()` at line 280 for actual certificate chain verification\n\n### Validation Type Breakdown:\n\n**Server Certificate Validation:**\n- `context_impl.cc` lines 164-185: Initializes verification mode through cert_validator\n- `default_validator.cc` lines 296-331: Performs actual X509_verify_cert() against trust store in doVerifyCertChain()\n- `spiffe_validator.cc` lines 149-192: Performs SPIFFE-specific server certificate validation\n\n**Client Certificate Validation:**\n- `default_validator.cc` lines 481-543: addClientValidationContext() sets client CA list, verification mode, and depth\n- `spiffe_validator.cc` lines 108-129: addClientValidationContext() sets client CA list for SPIFFE\n- Both use SSL_CTX_set_client_CA_list() to advertise acceptable CAs to clients\n- Both support optional client certificate requirement via verification mode flags\n\n### Validation Chain:\nThe certificate validation flow follows this call chain:\n1. ContextImpl constructor (context_impl.cc:68) initializes SSL_CTX and calls cert_validator->initializeSslContexts()\n2. SSL_CTX_set_custom_verify() registers customVerifyCallback as the verification callback\n3. During TLS handshake, OpenSSL invokes customVerifyCallback()\n4. customVerifyCallback() calls customVerifyCertChain()\n5. customVerifyCertChain() delegates to cert_validator->doVerifyCertChain()\n6. DefaultCertValidator::doVerifyCertChain() calls X509_verify_cert() for chain validation\n7. Additional validation checks performed by verifyCertificate() for SAN, hash, and SPKI verification"
}

